						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the temple of Bhīmēśvara.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1558 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1480, Kāḷayukti, Āshāḍha ba. 30, Monday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1558 A.D., July 15.</hi> The week-day, however, was <hi rend="bold">Friday.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged epigraph refers to a <hi rend="italic">sarvamānya</hi> gift to god Bhīmēśvara of Paruchūru by Gūḷappa-nāyanigāru, the <hi rend="italic">kāryakarta</hi> of Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara Rāmarājayya.</p>						

						</summary>
